		<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
		<div class="faq">
			<details>
				<summary>Is professional teeth whitening safe for my enamel?</summary>
				<p>Yes, when performed or supervised by a dentist, teeth whitening is extremely safe. We ensure the bleaching agent is applied correctly, protecting your gums and preserving your enamel.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>How long do porcelain veneers last?</summary>
				<p>With proper care and good oral hygiene, high-quality porcelain veneers can last 10 to 15 years, or even longer. They are highly resistant to stains compared to natural teeth.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>Will my insurance or the CDCP cover cosmetic dentistry?</summary>
				<p>No. Purely cosmetic procedures, such as whitening and veneers, are elective and are generally not covered by the CDCP or standard private dental insurance plans. We can discuss flexible payment options during your consultation.</p>
			</details>
